A few quick observations: Xalan loads its parser via JAXP. 
It normally ships with, and defaults to using, Xerces, but should be able to work with others. 
Xalan requires that xml-apis.jar 
be on the classpath. 
This is a first step toward factoring DOM, SAX, JAXP, TRAX, and related standardized code out of the individual Apache projects and into a shared library. 
See also the XML-COMMONS project at Apache for more information. 
